  "texts": [
    "Another emerging trend is the diversification of application domains.",
    "Earlier research focused mainly on stock markets and cryptocurrencies, but recent papers explore ML applications in FinTech profitability, policy forecasting, actuarial modeling, and even public investment allocation [42].",
    "This diversification shows that ML and DL are no longer confined to financial prediction but are becoming central to broader decision-support systems.",
    "However, despite this expansion, most studies remain empirical, and there is still limited theoretical development linking model outcomes to economic intuition.",
    "This highlights a gap between computational accuracy and financial interpretability that future research should address [43]."
